The future of SAA workers remains in limbo. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - SAA's Business Rescue practitioners have given employees an extension to sign voluntary termination agreements. The original deadline stipulated by the airline's Business Rescue Practitioners was 5pm on Friday. READ: SAA could shed staff from May 12 On Thursday the Labour court reserved judgment as the unions want the planned retrenchments to be declared unlawful. The SA Cabin Crew Association says workers have agreed to a wage cut to save SAA. Judgment has been reserved in the Labour Court in the case brought by worker unions Numsa and the SA Cabin Crew Association against embattled South African Airlines on Thursday. Courtesy of #DStv403